org.glassfish.jersey.client.rx

Interface RxClient<RX extends RxInvoker>

  • Type Parameters:
    RX - the concrete reactive invocation type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    javax.ws.rs.client.Client, javax.ws.rs.core.Configurable<javax.ws.rs.client.Client>

    public interface RxClient<RX extends RxInvoker>
extends javax.ws.rs.client.Client
    RxClient is the main entry point to the fluent API used to build and execute (reactive) client requests in order to consume responses returned.

    The Reactive Client APIs are enhanced with rx(...) methods on client invocation builder. These methods provide an entry point to invoke reactive requests. RxClient extension overrides methods of JAX-RS client to give user a way to access the reactive contracts.

    Since:
    2.13
    Author:
    Michal Gajdos, Marek Potociar (marek.potociar at oracle.com)
    See Also:
    Client, RxInvoker
